    "created_at": "2015-05-24T01:58:34Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-05-24T01:58:34Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I don't think we should override Ctrl-A, which already means something that people are generally used to. In general, we don't override any Ctrl shortcuts, because it almost always conflicts with something in the browser. The only exception we make is Ctrl-S, because browser save is not very useful on a notebook.\n\nIf you want to customise the shortcuts for your own use, that should be possible. @Carreau probably recalls the details of how to do that better than I do.\n\nFor an advanced example of customising keyboard shortcuts, see [ipython-vimception](https://github.com/ivanov/ipython-vimception).\n"
  },
