    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "CodeMirror supports emacs-like editing (with a couple of notable exceptions): https://codemirror.net/demo/emacs.html\n\nOne user added the following to ~/.ipython/profile_default/static/custom/custom.js\n\n`require([\"components/codemirror/keymap/emacs\"],\n     function (emacs) {\n         to('emacs');\n         console.log('emacs.js loaded');\n     });`\n\nBut this doesn't work for me.\n\nWhether a code editor should support standard emacs / vi shortcuts as the vast majority of users will expect is a no-brainer. I will submit a patch allowing you to choose emacs / vi from the menu once I figure out how to get it working.\n"
  },
